Key Match Events: Chicago Bulls guard Coby White threw down an emphatic slam over San Antonio Spurs superstar Victor Wembanyama.
After trailing by as much as 19 points, the Chicago Bulls stormed back to take down the San Antonio Spurs 114-110.
Zach LaVine led the way for Chicago, scoring 35 points with 10 rebounds and 8 assists.
Bulls guard Coby White scored 23 points and his night was highlighted by a monster slam over Spurs superstar Victor Wembanyama to ice the game with 15 seconds left.
Victor Wembanyama had an impressive performance with 23 points, 14 rebounds, and 8 blocks.
Post-Match Reflections: Zach LaVine expressed a mix of happiness and envy towards Coby White's highlight slam over Victor Wembanyama.
LaVine mentioned that they had a running joke about someone attempting to dunk over Wembanyama.
